Urinary extracellular vesicles and tubular transport.
Although uEVs hold the promise to advance the diagnosis of kidney disease to the molecular level, several biological and technical complexities still need to be addressed. The future will tell if uEV analysis will mainly be a powerful tool to study tubular physiology in humans or if it will move forward to become a diagnostic bedside test.
